sequenceDiagram
    participant Index as Models Index<br/>(YAML file)
    participant Extractor as model-extractor<br/>(Go CLI)
    participant HF as HuggingFace API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OCI as OCI Registry<br/>(registry.redhat.io)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant FS as Local Filesystem<br/>(output/ & data/)
    participant Report as metadata-report<br/>(Go CLI)
    participant Container as Data Container<br/>(ubi9-minimal)
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard<br/>(Volume Mount)

    Note over Index,Dashboard: Flow 1: Model Catalog Generation Pipeline

    Extractor->>Index: Read models-index.yaml
    Index-->>Extractor: Model image references

    loop For each model (max 5 concurrent)
        Extractor->>OCI: GET /v2/{repo}/manifests/{tag}
        OCI-->>Extractor: Container manifest
        Extractor->>OCI: GET /v2/{repo}/blobs/{digest}
        OCI-->>Extractor: Layer blob (modelcard)
        Extractor->>OCI: GET /v2/{repo}/blobs/{config-digest}
        OCI-->>Extractor: Config blob (timestamps, arch)
    end

    Note over Extractor,HF: HuggingFace Enrichment (optional, skip with --skip-huggingface)

    Extractor->>HF: GET /api/collections?owner=RedHatAI
    Note right of Extractor: Auth: Bearer HF_TOKEN (optional)
    HF-->>Extractor: Collection list

    loop For each model in collections
        Extractor->>HF: GET /api/models/{model-id}
        HF-->>Extractor: Model metadata (downloads, likes, tags, license)
        Extractor->>HF: GET /{model-id}/raw/main/README.md
        HF-->>Extractor: README YAML frontmatter
    end

    Extractor->>FS: Write extracted metadata (output/)
    Extractor->>FS: Write models-catalog.yaml (data/)
    Extractor->>FS: Write validated-models-catalog.yaml (data/)

    Note over Index,Dashboard: Flow 2: MCP Server Catalog Generation

    Extractor->>FS: Read MCP server input YAML (input/mcp_servers/)
    loop For each MCP server image
        Extractor->>OCI: GET /v2/{repo}/manifests/{tag}
        OCI-->>Extractor: Image manifest (arch, timestamps)
    end
    Extractor->>FS: Write redhat-mcp-servers-catalog.yaml (data/)

    Note over Index,Dashboard: Flow 3: Metadata Report

    Report->>FS: Read models-catalog.yaml & extraction output
    Report->>FS: Write completeness reports (MD + YAML)

    Note over Index,Dashboard: Flow 4: Container Image Data Access (Runtime)

    Note over Container: Built by Konflux<br/>YAML files copied into /app/data/
    Dashboard->>Container: Volume mount /app/data/
    Container-->>Dashboard: Catalog YAML files
